+ Executor Hierarchy (Java Concurrency)
    java.lang.Object
            |
    java.util.concurrent.Executor
            |
            |-- execute(Runnable)
            |
    java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService
            |
            |-- submit()
            |-- shutdown()
            |-- Future support
            |
    java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService
            |
            |-- schedule()
            |-- scheduleAtFixedRate()
            |-- scheduleWithFixedDelay()
    âš™ Implementation Classes
    ThreadPoolExecutor
            |
            |-- newFixedThreadPool
            |-- newCachedThreadPool
            |-- newSingleThreadExecutor


    ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor
            |
            |-- newScheduledThreadPool

    ğŸ‘‰ Executors methods are factory helpers
    ğŸ‘‰ Internally, everything uses ThreadPoolExecutor

+ CustomThreadFactory (From Example)
    Purpose:
    Control how threads are created
    Set thread name, priority, daemon flag

+ RejectedExecutionHandler (From Example)
    Used when:
    All threads are busy
    Queue is full
    Max thread limit reached

    âœ” Prevents system overload
    âœ” Allows fallback or logging logic

    ğŸ§  Key Takeaway (Very Important)

    ThreadPoolExecutor controls thread count, task queue, rejection policy, and lifecycle in one place